            <paragraph>Each string consist of three space separated values: "from" string, "to" string and integer offset. Each combination form the two string for a kerning pair, e.g, <literal>ab cd -3</literal> will create kerning pairs <literal>ac</literal>, <literal>ad</literal>, <literal>bc</literal>, and <literal>bd</literal> with offset <literal>-3</literal>. <literal>\uXXXX</literal> escape sequences can be used to add Unicode characters.</paragraph>
